This paper deals with sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as support vector machines (SVM) and word2vec, which are commonly used in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of supervised learning and feature extraction, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the creation of embeddings, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CY) and is also relevant to NLP.
